def: Living a long time; of great age. Sir T. Browne.
A game, match, etc., open only to losers in early stages ofcontests.
A branch of algebra which relates to the direct search forunknown quantities. [R.]
A female waiter or attendant; a waiting maid or waiting woman.
Any one of several species of sparoid fishes belonging toSargus, Pomodasys, and related genera; -- called also sar, andsaragu.
Of or pertaining to bards, or their poetry. "The bardic lays ofancient Greece." G. P. Marsh.
